headline: NetApp (NTAP) Is Up 5.1% After Deepening AWS AI Ties While Maintaining Capital Returns - What's Changed
summary: In late November and early December 2025, NetApp reported second-quarter fiscal 2026 results with modest year-over-year revenue and earnings growth, confirmed full-year guidance, affirmed a US$0.52 per-share dividend for January 2026, and disclosed ongoing buybacks alongside an ESOP-related shelf registration of up to US$980.64 million in common stock. Shortly after, NetApp introduced a new capability that lets enterprises tap AWS AI and analytics services directly against FSx for NetApp...
